OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FDon't say 'panic' amid fuel
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fcrisis, Cabinet Office     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fwarns councils             
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The government has advised councils not
OL,6, to use the phrases "panic" or "panic   
OL,7, buying" about fuel supply problems,    
OL,8, documents seen by the BBC reveal.      
OL,10,FSlides prepared by the Cabinet Office's
OL,11,FBehavioural Science Team also advised  
OL,12,Fagainst using language that morally    
OL,13,Fjudges people buying petrol.           
OL,15,FA Green Party council leader called the
OL,16,Frecommendations "nonsensical".         
OL,18,FThe government said it worked "closely 
OL,19,Fwith councils... on communications to  
OL,20,Fencourage a co-ordinated response."    
